%spark.pyspark

# define the data source
gs_df = sqlContext.read.parquet("/hadoop/gaia/parquet/gdr2/gaia_source/*.parquet")

# register as SQL-queryable 
gs_df.createOrReplaceTempView("gaia_source")

# make the query
sql_df = spark.sql("SELECT FLOOR(source_id / 562949953421312) AS hpx5, COUNT(*) AS n FROM gaia_source GROUP BY hpx5")

%spark.pyspark

# plot up the sky counts
import numpy as np
import healpy as hp

# healpy constants
NSIDE = 32
NPIX = hp.nside2npix(NSIDE)

# do the visualisation
array_data = np.empty(NPIX)
for item in sql_df.rdd.collect():  array_data[item[0]] = item[1]
hp.mollview(array_data, nest=True, title='Gaia DR2 source counts at HEALPix level 5', cmap='viridis', norm = 'log')
hp.graticule(coord='E', color='white')
